<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS' SOCCER ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In other Sunset League games: 
</P>
<P>
 Edison 2, Ocean View 0 -- Phil Urkrov scored both goals for seventh-ranked 
Edison (15-2-1, 7-2). Roy Ludt had three saves for the Chargers. 
</P>
<P>
 Fountain Valley 5, Servite 0 -- Joey Vasquez scored twice and Brent Futagaki, 
Dean Kojima and Mo Danban each added a goal for Fountain Valley (4-8-4, 2-4-3). 
Servite drops to 6-9, 4-5. 
</P>
<P>
 Marina 3, Westminster 1 -- Jose Monroy scored two goals for sixth-ranked 
Marina. Joey Samples scored third goal for Marina, which improves to 13-4, 8-1. 
Westminster drops to 6-10, 3-6. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Sea View League: 
</P>
<P>
 Corona del Mar 5, University 1 -- Paul Fruchbom, Roberto Intriago, Jed 
Weinstein and Dustin Lee each scored one goal and Justin McKibben recorded 
three saves to lead Corona del Mar (14-2-3, 7-0-1), the top-ranked team in the 
county. The Sea Kings also scored on an own goal. 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine 3, Newport Harbor 1 -- Kevin McLain had two goals and an assist and 
Grant Donaldson added a goal and an assist to lead visiting Irvine (9-7-1, 
3-4-1). 
</P>
<P>
 Dominic Frantantaro scored for Newport Harbor (4-9-4, 2-5-1). 
</P>
<P>
 Saddleback 1, Tustin 0 -- Carlos Vizcaino scored a first-half goal for 
fourth-ranked Saddleback (13-24, 5-0-1). Dwayne Stokes had 10 saves for Tustin 
(8-5-2, 3-3-2). 
</P>
<P>
 Woodbridge 1, Santa Margarita 1 -- Gustaf Gratzer scored the tying goal for 
Woodbridge (6-5-4, 1-4-3). Mike Allred scored for Santa Margarita, which is 
ranked sixth in Orange County. Jason Hause had nine saves for the Warriors 
(6-5-4, 1-4-3). 
</P>
<P>
 In the South Coast League: 
</P>
<P>
 Mater Dei 3, Dana Hills 0 -- John Gurdeis scored two goals for Mater Dei, the 
second-ranked team in Orange County. Ryan Chaput scored the other goal for the 
Monarchs (17-1-3, 4-1-1). 
</P>
