<HEADLINE>
<P>
CAPISTRANO VALLEY UPSETS EL TORO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Capistrano Valley, which upset top-ranked Mater Dei last week in boys' soccer, 
again played the role of spoiler by beating eighth-ranked El Toro, 2-1, in a 
South Coast League game Wednesday at El Toro High. 
</P>
<P>
 Chris Tullar and Dustin Layne scored second-half goals for Capistrano Valley 
(11-5-3, 3-2-1 in league), which trailed, 1-0, at halftime. Mirko Vuksic had 
five saves for the Cougars. Wade Fraser scored for El Toro. 
</P>
<P>
 With the victory, the Cougars moved into a tie for second place with El Toro, 
which dropped to 13-3-4, 3-2-1. 
</P>
