<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; GOLDEN WEST WOMEN EXTEND WINNING STEAK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE KRESAL, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Julie Murdent and Nicole Quinn gave Golden West a strong inside advantage and 
helped the Rustlers to a 65-55 victory over Fullerton in an Orange Empire 
Conference women's game Wednesday at Golden West. 
</P>
<P>
 The victory gives Golden West (24-3, 6-0 in conference) a two-game lead at the 
halfway point in the conference race. 
</P>
<P>
 It was the 23rd consecutive conference victory and the 64th consecutive home 
victory for Golden West, the top-ranked team in Southern California. Fullerton 
was the last team to beat Golden West at home when the Hornets did it in 1989. 
</P>
<P>
 Murdent, a freshman forward from Fountain Valley High, had 22 points, 
including 14 in the second half. Quinn, a freshman reserve forward from 
Woodbridge High, had a season-high 19 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Golden West was able to control the game because of strong rebounding. The 
Rustlers held a 75-30 advantage in rebounding, including a 45-12 margin in the 
second half. 
</P>
<P>
 Murdent had 15 rebounds, 12 offensive, and Kristin Brun and Katie Miner had 14 
rebounds each. Brun also scored 11 points, her high this season in conference 
play. 
</P>
<P>
 "It was another ugly win for us," Golden West Coach Dave Stricklin said. "We 
haven't shot well for a while now. But someone always seems to step up. 
Tonight, it was Nicole Quinn. It's been exciting for us as coaches to get to 
the gym each night and see who it's going to be." 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton (16-11, 4-2) got within 52-47 with 6 minutes 21 seconds left but 
Golden West went on a 9-0 run. Quinn had five points and Murdent had four in 
the run. 
</P>
<P>
 In other Orange Empire Conference women's games: 
</P>
<P>
 Orange Coast 82, Rancho Santiago 50 -- Coach Mike Thornton, in his fifth 
season at Orange Coast, got his 100th career victory. Thornton, who guided OCC 
to its first appearance in the State tournament last season, has a career mark 
of 100-51. LeAnn Kazmer, who missed last Friday's game because of a sore knee, 
scored a game-high 26 points for Orange Coast (16-9, 4-2). 
</P>
<P>
 Riverside 62, Cypress 60 -- Audrey McMurry got a rebound with 18 seconds left 
and host Riverside (20-8, 3-3) was able to run out the clock. McMurry finished 
with 20 points. Yolanda Hearvey (15 points) made two free throws with about 30 
seconds left to cut the lead to 61-60. 
</P>
<P>
 In Orange Empire Conference men's games: 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton 94, Golden West 80 -- Tyrone Merriweather, a sophomore forward, 
scored 30 points and added 11 rebounds for host Fullerton (20-6, 5-2), which 
has won five in a row. Kevin Carlson added 16 points for the Hornets. 
</P>
<P>
 Tobie Priest had 21 and Greg Vanden Ordel added 18 for Golden West (8-14, 
1-6). 
</P>
<P>
 Rancho Santiago 88, Orange Coast 66 -- Sean Amos scored 23 points and Nathan 
Small had 15 for Rancho Santiago (16-8, 4-3). Chauncey Woolridge scored 34 
points and had nine rebounds for Orange Coast (1-11, 1-6). 
</P>
<P>
 Riverside 71, Cypress 69 (OT) -- Cypress' Mike McGuire missed a three-pointer 
and teammate Jim Falletta missed a tip-in as time ran out. Host Cypress (10-16, 
1-6) scored the final five points of regulation to force overtime. 
</P>
<P>
 Jeff Cummins had 17 points for Cypress and Darryle Flicking had 19 for 
Riverside (20-5, 6-1). 
</P>
</TEXT>
