<HEADLINE>
<P>
GOLF TOURNAMENT TO START FRIDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Golfers from the Nike and PGA tours will join amateur partners Friday and 
Saturday for the 20th Taco Bell Newport Classic at the Newport Beach Country 
Club. 
</P>
<P>
 PGA Tour player Bob May of La Habra, PGA Tour winner Sam Randolph and Paul 
Goydos, who finished tied for eighth in the recent Hawaiian Open, will be among 
the players competing for the $13,000 first prize in the pro-am event, which 
begins at 7 a.m. each day and is free to spectators. 
</P>
<P>
 The tournament will include a free clinic by Leadbetter Golf Academy pro Brian 
Mogg Friday at 3:30 p.m. on the club's driving range. 
</P>
<P>
 Proceeds will benefit Hoag Hospital's Emergency Care Unit. 
</P>
