<P>
 "No, they don't. They make even sex sound boring nowadays." 
</P>
<P>
 Jeremy Rex, 17 
</P>
<P>
 junior, El Modena 
</P>
<P>
 "In today's politically correct world, no one is daring to dig into these 
subjects for fear of repercussions. As a result, the classes really teach us 
nothing. But most importantly, this gives us the impression that society really 
doesn't care -- that what we are doing right now is fine." 
</P>
<P>
 Richard Kim, 15 
</P>
<P>
 sophomore, Villa Park 
</P>
<P>
 "I didn't learn anything I didn't already know." 
</P>
