</P>
<P>
 junior, Sonora 
</P>
<P>
 "Sex ed courses in school only cover the physical side to having sex. They 
teach you about protection from diseases and pregnancy, but fail to deal with 
the mental part of having sex. Many teens have sex before they are mentally 
ready to deal with it, because they feel they have to in order to keep their 
boyfriend with them. Teachers need to stress that sex is a big step in a 
relationship and unless teens are completely sure they want to and that they 
can be mature about it, they are not ready." 
</P>
<P>
