<HEADLINE>
<P>
INSIDE LINE: D.A.N.C.E. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Looking for something to do in a drug-free, alcohol-free environment? You 
might want to check out D.A.N.C.E. (Drug Alternative Nights and Counseling 
Events). 
</P>
<P>
 Activities include trips to amusement parks, ice and roller skating rinks and 
dances. Services include counseling for family problems and drug or alcohol 
abuse. 
</P>
<P>
 D.A.N.C.E. was the brainchild of former Los Alamitos High School student 
Dannah L. Sachs. It is now run by her brother, Nate. Events include adult 
supervision. 
</P>
<P>
 Activities are open to students from all high schools and usually attract 
between 270 to 550 people.  
</P>
<P>
 For information, call Los Alamitos Youth Center at (310) 493-4043. 
</P>
<P>
 Jennie Timar , junior, Los Alamitos High School  
</P>
