<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWS BITES : GET OUTTA HERE, ETHYLENE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The problem with buying fruits and vegetables in bulk is that you don't always 
use them fast enough to justify the savings.Evert-Fresh bags are transparent 
plastic bags lined with processed Japanese oya stone, a cousin of zeolite, 
which absorbs the ethylene gases that cause discoloration in fruits and 
vegetables (and flowers, for that matter), extending their life for weeks. The 
reusable bags have also been given an anti-fogging treatment that minimizes 
moisture, inhibits bacteria growth and reduces Vitamin C loss up to 50%. 
Available in packages of 10 at health food stores. Flightless Bird Rides High 
</P>
<P>
 Qantas, the Australian airline, serves emu -- a smaller cousin of the ostrich 
-- in first class. 
</P>
