A LOAF FOUND LACKING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I tried your recipe for herb ham loaf ("Who Will Speak for Ham?" Jan. 6) and 
found it wanting.From my long years of experience I've found that one needs 
something like cracker or bread crumbs to hold the meatloaf together. The herb 
ham loaf recipe had none and the result is a crumbly meat concoction that may 
be good for stuffing green peppers or baked eggplant. 
</P>
<P>
 MRS. DAVID KROFFE 
</P>
