<HEADLINE>
<P>
OUT AND ABOUT: TARTS AND FLOWERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRISTINA V. GODBEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Here's a flower shop with a twist: It doubles as a restaurant. 
</P>
<P>
 At the Rita Flora Kitchen and Flower Shop, the aroma of fresh flowers is 
rivaled only by the culinary offerings. 
</P>
<P>
 Located at La Brea Avenue and 6th Street in Los Angeles, Rita Flora offers a 
menu complete with muffins, sandwiches, specialties and salad plates. Popular 
choices include cheese tortellini with pesto, steamed vegetables and Thai 
noodles with chicken in peanut sauce. (Selections range from $5.25 to $7.95). 
Top it off with a dessert, such as a chocolate brownie or sugar-free fruit 
tart, which are baked fresh daily. 
</P>
<P>
 While customers savor gourmet delights and sip frothy espressos, they sit on 
tall stools, gazing out on the busy street. 
</P>
<P>
 "I have always liked the atmosphere," said Lisa Annala, a semiregular 
customer. "There is no place like it in the area. It's a casual place . . . 
being around the flowers is great, the doors open out (onto the street) and the 
menu is good." 
</P>
<P>
 Owner Rita Azar opened Rita Flora six years ago. When the space next door 
became available three years later, she expanded and opened the restaurant 
portion, which has enjoyed enormous success, both for dining and takeout. 
</P>
<P>
 During the day, the clientele varies from business and entertainment 
executives to neighborhood residents. Patrons can read, chat or people-watch 
without interruption. And, of course, they can buy flowers. 
</P>
<P>
 Wayne Pepper, who stopped by for a quick lunch last Friday, said: "I like to 
get flowers for my wife afterward." 
</P>
<P>
 Rita Flora Kitchen/Flower Shop is located at 460 S. La Brea Ave., Los Angeles. 
Hours are 8 a.m. to midnight daily. Flowers cannot be purchased after 10 p.m. 
(213) 931-9900. CHRISTINA V. GODBEY 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Infobox 
</P>
</TYPE>
