<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Eric Lichtbla; Jan Herman, GRANELLI, ; Leslie Berkman 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 JUST DUCKY: After the media beating Disney took over its Euro Disney Resort 
and Virginia theme park projects, the Burbank brigade could use some good 
reviews. They get one in the current New Yorker, as the literary, high-brow 
weekly offers a lengthy and glowing assessment of the Mighty Ducks' performance 
on the ice and their marketing wizardry off it. . . . But Disney did take one 
hit: The Iceman, the ill-fated team mascot that lasted all of one game in 
Anaheim, was blasted in the piece as a "major dork-o-rama." 
</P>
<P>
 PAST DUE: South Africa's most prominent playwright, Athol Fugard, says he's 
thinking about a trip to Costa Mesa for the revival of his latest work at South 
Coast Repertory. (OC LIVE!) "Playland" opens Friday and runs through Feb. 27. . 
. . While the county's only professional resident company has done three other 
Fugard plays, he has never shown up. "I owe them," admits Fugard, who 
revolutionized South African theater decades ago by putting blacks and whites 
on the same stage. 
</P>
<P>
 D.C. CONNECTION: Irvine PR man Bob Nelson caught some flak from fellow 
Republicans when he broke ranks to support Bill Clinton's 1992 campaign, but it 
has paid off. First he helped on the Clinton transition, and now he's been 
named to an economic panel that advises the President and Congress on U.S. 
competitiveness abroad. . . . The only drawback, he says: often "nightmarish" 
FBI background checks on such issues as domestic help. "It's just irritating. I 
can sure appreciate Bobby Inman's feelings." 
</P>
<P>
 NO YOLKING MATTER: If you like your eggs soft-boiled or sunny side up, beware: 
the County Health Care Agency last year received 91 reports of salmonella 
enteritidis . . . . The disease comes from eating under-cooked, infected eggs. 
The county's Dr. Hildy Meyers says such incidents, transmitted from infected 
hens, are increasing steadily. Symptoms: fever, diarrhea and nausea. 
</P>
