<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN SHOT AFTER POINTING GUN AT OFFICERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man who allegedly pointed a gun at plainclothes police officers in 
South-Central Los Angeles was shot and critically wounded by one of the 
officers Wednesday afternoon, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Stephen Meigham, 21, was driving along Avalon Boulevard next to the unmarked 
patrol car when he said something to the officers and pointed a handgun at 
them, said Lt. William Hall, who heads the Los Angeles Police Department's 
officer-involved shooting section. 
</P>
<P>
 "It appeared that Meigham was upset," Hall said. 
</P>
<P>
 Officer Ray Morales fired six rounds out the window of the police car at 
Meigham, who drove on for a short distance until he ran into a parked car, Hall 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Meigham was taken to California Medical Center at 14th and Hope streets, where 
he was being treated for bullet wounds to the head and a hand. 
</P>
<P>
 "There is no explanation as to why Meigham pointed the gun at officers," Hall 
said. "It is also not known if Meigham even knew they were officers." 
</P>
