<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: OXNARD; BUSINESSMAN NAMED NEW CHAMBER LEADER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRED ALVAREZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Oxnard businessman Don Facciano has been named executive director of the 
Oxnard Chamber of Commerce after the resignation of Penny Hoffman, chamber 
officials announced Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Facciano, 57, who recently ended a 35-year career with Sears, Roebuck & Co., 
will assume his new duties Feb. 22.Hoffman's last day is Feb. 21. 
</P>
<P>
 "We wanted to make this a continuous flow," said Facciano, a longtime chamber 
member. "We are not going to drop a step, we are not going to pause the 
momentum that has been gathered under Penny." 
</P>
<P>
 Hoffman, who became executive director of the chamber last May, said she 
resigned her post after her husband, Eric, accepted a position as president and 
partner of a Kansas City pharmaceutical company. 
</P>
<P>
 Hoffman said she has applied for an executive director's position at a small 
chamber of commerce in the Kansas City area. 
</P>
<P>
 "It was obviously something that was not planned," Hoffman said of her 
departure. "We thought we would be in California forever." 
</P>
<P>
 Hoffman said she is most proud of the chamber's role in reopening the city's 
tourism bureau and of the effort to put the chamber office under the same roof 
as the newly formed Greater Oxnard Economic Development Corp. and the Greater 
Oxnard and Harbors Tourism Bureau. 
</P>
<P>
 Those three agencies will be housed at Oxnard's Heritage Square starting March 
1. 
</P>
<P>
 "I think I was just starting to make a little bit of a difference," she said. 
"Now I don't get to stay to see the fruits of my labor." FRED ALVAREZ 
</P>
</TEXT>
