<HEADLINE>
<P>
UNDESERVED CREDIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 It seems there is no situation that Congressman Elton Gallegly will not 
exploit to make political hay. 
</P>
<P>
 In a recent essay he states that Ventura County was declared an earthquake 
disaster zone "within minutes" after he appealed to President Clinton at the 
town hall meeting. 
</P>
<P>
 I watched that meeting on C-SPAN and I saw Vicky Howard, county supervisor 
from Simi Valley, make an appeal and I saw Sen. Barbara Boxer's visible 
increase in attention when she heard the words Ventura County. Having played a 
significant role in helping with her election, I know that Ventura County is a 
special place for Boxer.  
</P>
<P>
 Can one imagine that some credit be given the supervisor from Simi and the 
senator from California, who has consistently supported Clinton's programs, 
rather than be given entirely to Gallegly who has primarily played the part of 
a Clinton obstructionist? 
</P>
<P>
 RIKKI HORNE 
</P>
<P>
 Ojai 
