<HEADLINE>
<P>
TRUCK HAULING VCRS HIJACKED, DRIVER BOUND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ventura County sheriff's deputies Wednesday found a truck driver tied up 
inside the cab of his vehicle in Newbury Park, a few hours after robbers 
hijacked the truck and stole its trailer full of videocassette recorders, 
deputies reported. 
</P>
<P>
 Pedro Cardova of Long Beach had picked up a container of VCRs at the Port of 
Long Beach early Wednesday and was driving north on the Long Beach Freeway, 
when three men in a black Oldsmobile signaled that he had a problem with his 
truck, a Sheriff's Department spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
 After Cardova pulled over to the side of the road, sheriff's deputies said one 
of the men in the Oldsmobile forced his way into the cab of the truck by 
pointing a gun at Cardova. 
</P>
<P>
 Cardova was tied up and his face was covered by the gunman, the spokesman 
said. The gunman then drove the truck to an unknown location where the trailer 
with the container filled with VCRs was unhooked from the truck, the spokesman 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 One of the suspects then drove the truck to Newbury Park and left it near the 
intersection of Anchor Court and Rancho Conejo Boulevard, where Cardova was 
eventually found, the spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
 The case is being referred to the Long Beach Police Department for 
investigation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
