<P>
METRO FOCUS: DOWNTOWN; ELDERLY MAN SHOT TO DEATH, WIFE WOUNDED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An elderly man was shot to death and his wife was seriously wounded Wednesday 
in an apparent burglary at their home, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police found Rupert Thompson, 73, lying in the front lawn of his home in the 
11100 block of Aqua Vista Street about 1:10 a.m., dead of a single gunshot 
wound to the head, said Los Angeles Police Officer Ron Russell. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said Thompson also was beaten, possibly with the handgun used in his 
murder. 
</P>
<P>
 Dorothy Thompson, 70, suffered a gunshot wound to the shoulder and was taken 
to a local hospital where she was admitted to the intensive care unit and 
listed in stable condition, Russell said. 
</P>
<P>
 Dorothy Thompson told police that she thought the gunshots she heard were the 
sound of another aftershock or something connected with earthquake relief 
activities, Russell said. 
