<P>
SIMI VALLEY HIGH OFFICIALS UNCERTAIN WHO WILL COACH IN BRADSHAW'S ABSENCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JASON H. REID 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 With basketball Coach Dean Bradshaw's status unclear for Friday night's game 
against Camarillo because of an altercation with a player, Simi Valley High 
officials are uncertain who will coach the team when it returns to play for the 
first time in two weeks. 
</P>
<P>
 Bradshaw is suspended while the Simi Valley Unified School District conducts 
its investigation of the incident, in which Bradshaw shoved senior guard Sam 
Rodriguez during a 51-44 league victory over Westlake on Jan. 14.The game 
marked the last time Simi Valley has played because of problems related to the 
Jan. 17 earthquake and Bradshaw's situation. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's doubtful the situation will be resolved by Friday," Athletic Director 
George Ragsdale said. "We're not sure who will coach the team. Chances are I 
might coach." 
</P>
<P>
 Pioneer junior varsity Coach Steve Johnson and sophomore team Coach Christian 
Aurand are also candidates. 
</P>
<P>
 Simi Valley is scheduled to play host to the Marmonte League game at 7:30 at 
the Apollo Continuation School in Simi Valley. JASON H. REID 
</P>
