<HEADLINE>
<P>
AUTO ACCIDENT KILLS HUSBAND OF JACKIE SPEIER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From a Times Staff Writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The husband of Assemblywoman Jackie Speier (D-Burlingame) has died of injuries 
he suffered in an automobile accident, her office announced Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Dr. Steven K. Sierra, 52, who married Speier in 1987, died late Tuesday night 
after a crash several hours earlier in which he was broadsided by a driver who 
apparently ran a red light at a San Mateo intersection.Speier, 43, has 
represented part of San Francisco and San Mateo counties for seven years. 
</P>
<P>
 Sierra earned his medical degree with honors from UC San Francisco in 1973 and 
was an emergency room doctor. 
</P>
<P>
 The driver of the other car was identified by authorities as Thomas Rivera 
III, 24, of Burlingame. He suffered minor injuries. No citation was issued, but 
an investigation into the accident was continuing. 
</P>
<P>
 Speier recently dropped out of the secretary of state's race because she is 
pregnant with the couple's second child. 
</P>
