<P>
BRIEFCASE: MARKETING; TRADE GROUP CHAPTER ALLOWS CALLERS TO PUSH BUTTONS AND 
RECEIVE FAXES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Anne Michaud, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Orange County chapter of the American Marketing Assn. is proving itself 
worthy of the name.The chapter recently set up a telephone line to send faxes 
to callers who push the appropriate phone keys. 
</P>
<P>
 The system eliminates the need for office space or a receptionist, creator 
Steve Fox said. The association is the first customer for Fox's Irvine-based 
company, On Demand America. 
</P>
<P>
 A former computer hardware salesman, Fox said he wanted to find a different 
line of work. He set up a bank of personal computers to route information 
automatically to fax machines. Fox is currently adding two customers, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 The marketing association's number -- (800) 329-7262 -- sends information 
about meetings, membership and a job hot line. 
</P>
