<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: MARKETING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Anne Michaud, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Writing Their Congressmen: A Laguna Hills-based political consultant, Adler 
Wilson Campaign Services Inc., has designed a computer databank thats allowed 
more than 30,000 home builders to contact their congressional representatives 
last weekend. 
</P>
<P>
 The databank was used by the the National Assn. of Home Builders during its 
annual meeting in Las Vegas. Attendees were able to enter their home addresses, 
find the names of their representatives, and create letters on a personalized 
letterhead. 
</P>
<P>
 The wording of the seven letters varied, Jeff Adler said, but each made the 
point that association members would like to see regulations eased that prevent 
the cutting of trees. Lumber prices have increased 67% in the past five months 
because of limited supply, the letters said. 
</P>
