<P>
YORBA LINDA BROKER BARRED FROM NYSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Robert Jenican of Yorba Linda has been censured and barred permanently from 
the New York Stock Exchange, the exchange announced Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 The exchange said Jenican misappropriated customer funds, issued false account 
statements to customers and failed to give the exchange a written explanation 
it had asked for. 
</P>
<P>
 Jenican was fired from an unidentified brokerage that is a member of the 
exchange. He consented to the ruling without admitting or denying guilt. He 
declined to comment when reached Wednesday. 
</P>
