<HEADLINE>
<P>
SANTA ANA PLANT TO CLOSE, MOVE JOBS TO OKLAHOMA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN O'DELL, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Bridge Products Inc. said it will close its Santa Ana manufacturing plant by 
this summer and transfer up to 35 jobs to an existing facility it owns in 
Muskogee, Okla. 
</P>
<P>
 Bridge's Camel Tire Products division decided more than a year ago to close 
the Santa Ana plant, which it leases.The company makes tire patches and other 
tire products. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition to 17 to 20 hourly manufacturing and support jobs, about 10 to 15 
customer service and administration jobs now at the Santa Ana facility will be 
centralized in Muskogee, and positions in accounting, purchasing and marketing 
will be added, said Bruce Garringer, Camel's vice president and chief financial 
officer. 
</P>
<P>
 California employees will have first chance at the Muskogee jobs, he said. The 
company said the plant closure was ordered to improve service, enhance Camel's 
competitiveness and cut costs. 
</P>
<P>
 The Muskogee site, which will become Bridge Products' Aftermarket Components 
Division, will absorb roughly half of the products formerly manufactured in 
Santa Ana. A company plant in Alta Vista, Va., will take over the rest. 
</P>
<P>
 The Muskogee facility will become the main distribution center for Bridge, but 
Garringer said the Chicago-based company will retain a warehouse, distribution 
and sales facility somewhere in Southern California. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA012794-0302 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 007713 </DOCID>
