<HEADLINE>
<P>
LIVE BUT UNARMED MINE DISCOVERED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A city sanitation crew clearing a storm drain in preparation for the rainy 
season discovered a live but unarmed Claymore anti-personnel mine Wednesday, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
 A bomb disposal unit from the El Toro Marine Corps Air Station, with 
assistance from the sheriff's bomb squad, removed the mine without incident 
about 3 p.m., Irvine Police Lt. Al Muir said.  
</P>
<P>
 Muir said police had no idea how long the mine had been in the storm drain at 
Turtle Rock Drive and Sycamore Creek or how it got there. 
</P>
<P>
 A model still being used by the Marines, the mine was live but did not have 
the electrical impulse device necessary to detonate it, Muir said. 
</P>
