<HEADLINE>
<P>
ARENA NAMED BEST NEW CONCERT VENUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE BOEHM 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The readers of Poll Star magazine, a trade publication widely read in the 
concert industry, have named the Anaheim Arena the best new concert venue to 
open in 1993. 
</P>
<P>
 Gary Bongiovanni, editor of the Fresno-based magazine, said that the arena won 
out over four other nominees, including the Glen Helen Blockbuster Pavilion in 
San Bernardino County. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's definitely a coup for us," said arena spokesman John Nicoletti. "It's 
nice to know we're thought of as a major player among all the new venues around 
the world." 
</P>
<P>
 Poll Star draws its national readership from the ranks of concert promoters, 
artist managers, booking agents, record company staffers and building managers. 
</P>
<P>
 The award, a plexiglass plaque, was conferred at ceremonies Monday night at 
the Paramount in New York City. MIKE BOEHM 
</P>
