<HEADLINE>
<P>
CITY HALL JOURNAL: CERRITOS; CITY TO PAY MORE FOR SCHOOL GYM EXPANSION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN POPE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city has agreed to pay an additional $524,000 to expand the Cerritos High 
School gymnasium for use by students and residents. 
</P>
<P>
 The city previously agreed to provide $2 million for the expansion, which 
would double the size of the gymnasium by adding a second regulation-size 
basketball court.The lowest bid on the project, however, was about $2.5 
million. Officials will draw the additional money from the city's reserve fund, 
said Mayor John Crawley. ABC Unified School District will provide maintenance 
and upkeep. 
</P>
<P>
 The school district will use the enlarged gym on school days until 5:15 p.m., 
when the city will take over until 10 p.m. On non-school days and in the 
summer, the city will be able to use the gym from 8 a.m. to 10 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Construction is expected to begin in about three weeks and to be completed in 
about a year. JOHN POPE 
</P>
